button.mdl-button.mdl-button--icon.mdl-button--accent(action='#', onclick='edit.showDialog("consent-info")'): i.material-icons help_outline
dialog.mdl-dialog(id='consent-info')
  h4.mdl-dialog__title Obtaining Consent
  .mdl-dialog__content
    p.
      Research studies that involve human subjects typically require some form of ethics
      review. Depending on the country, this may be review by an institutional review
      board (IRB), or by an ethics committee (EC). For some studies, consent may be required
      to conduct a research study, which means that the researcher must ensure that each
      participant is fully informed about the nature of the study, and must obtain a signed
      consent from each participant. Additionally, consent may be required as a condition
      of app review.
    p See the #[a(href='http://researchkit.org/docs/docs/InformedConsent/InformedConsent.html', target='_blank') ResearchKit guide] #[i.material-icons(style='font-size: 1em') launch] for further information.
    .mdl-dialog__actions
      button.mdl-button.mdl-button--colored.mdl-js-button.close(type='button') OK
  script dialogPolyfill.registerDialog(document.getElementbyId('consent-info'));
.mdl-grid(id='steps')
  .mdl-cell.step
    .statusbar Carrier &bull;&bull;&bull;&bull;&bull;
    .statusbar(style='text-align: center; right: 5px') 3:30 PM
    .statusbar(style='text-align: right; right: 5px; text-align: right')
      i.material-icons(style='font-size: 1.5em; transform: rotate(90deg)') battery_std
    .content
      .title Welcome
      .summary(contenteditable='true').
        Replace this with an introduction to the survey which the users are joining.
        This should be a short explanation of the consent flow which will follow. The
        in-depth explanation can go in the full description which is accessible from the
        "learn more" link below.
      .more: a(href='#', onclick='edit.showDialog("step-more-stepId")') Learn more about this study first
    .next Get Started
  dialog.mdl-dialog(id='step-more-stepId')
    h4.mdl-dialog__title Learn more
    .mdl-dialog__content
      p.
        The learn more page is shown when the user presses the "learn more" link below
        the summary at a given step in a consent document. It should provide comprehensive
        documentation of everything involved in consenting to this step in the consent
        document.
      p.
        The content of this step of the consent document can take the form of plain text
        or #[a(href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Markdown', target='_blank') markdown] 
        #[i.material-icons(style='font-size: 1em') launch] syntax.
      textarea(id='step-content-stepId', style='width: 100%; min-height: 200px').
        # Welcome

        Replace this with complete documentation of everything involved in consenting to this step in the consent document.
      //- div(id='step-editor-stepId', style='width: 100%; min-height: 200px')
      .mdl-dialog__actions
        button.mdl-button.mdl-button--colored.mdl-js-button.close(type='button') Done
  script dialogPolyfill.registerDialog(document.getElementbyId("step-more-stepId"));
      
